{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778975583570,"sessionID":"ses_1cccff35bffef2xqhPYhjIHD90","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_OWhuRku8EsjGUIi2CRxXR0iu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Updated the life stage bridge axiom generation to use `in taxon` (`RO:0002162`) consistently for life cycle and life cycle stage terms, and refreshed the affected checked-in bridge products. Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+## Summary\n+\n+This change addresses issue #3409 by making life stage bridge axioms use `in taxon` (`RO:0002162`) instead of `occurs in` (`BFO:0000066`). This matches the discussion consensus that `in taxon` should be used for linking life cycle and life cycle stage terms to their taxon-specific counterparts.\n+\n+## Changes\n+\n+- Updated `src/ontology/bridge/bridges.rules` so descendants of `UBERON:0000104` (`life cycle`) and `UBERON:0000105` (`life cycle stage`) set `TAXREL` to `RO:0002162`.\n+- Updated the dedicated XAO life-stage bridge rule in `src/ontology/bridge/bridge-xao-ls.rules` to generate `RO:0002162 some NCBITaxon:8353`.\n+- Updated the older bridge-generation scripts in `src/scripts/` and `src/ontology/` so life-cycle xrefs use `in_taxon` rather than `occurs_in` when that path is used.\n+- Refreshed the affected checked-in bridge OWL products so existing life-stage bridge axioms now use `RO_0002162`:\n+  - `uberon-bridge-to-fbdv.owl`\n+  - `uberon-bridge-to-wbls.owl`\n+  - `uberon-bridge-to-xao.owl`\n+  - `uberon-bridge-to-zfs.owl`\n+  - `uberon-bridge-to-sslso.owl`\n+\n+## Validation\n+\n+- Verified relevant identifiers in the local ontology context, including `UBERON:0000104`, `UBERON:0000105`, `RO:0002162`, and `BFO:0000066`.\n+- Confirmed the affected generated bridge files no longer contain `BFO_0000066` in the life-stage bridge products that were changed.\n+- Ran Perl syntax checks on both bridge-generation script copies.\n+- Regenerated the SSSOM/T-OWL bridge rules from `taxa.py` successfully.\n+- Validated modified bridge OWL syntax with `robot convert`.\n+- Ran ELK reasoning with `robot reason --reasoner ELK` on each modified bridge OWL file.\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+- [x] Read issue context and comments.\n+- [x] Identified the rule path responsible for taxon-specific bridge generation.\n+- [x] Updated the generic and XAO-specific life-stage bridge rules.\n+- [x] Updated legacy xref bridge script behavior for life-cycle xrefs.\n+- [x] Refreshed affected checked-in bridge products.\n+- [x] Performed syntax, identifier, and reasoning validation.\n+\n+@dragon-ai-agent\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,1 @@\n+Updated the life stage bridge axiom generation to use `in taxon` (`RO:0002162`) consistently for life cycle and life cycle stage terms, and refreshed the affected checked-in bridge products. Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+## Summary\n+\n+This change addresses issue #3409 by making life stage bridge axioms use `in taxon` (`RO:0002162`) instead of `occurs in` (`BFO:0000066`). This matches the discussion consensus that `in taxon` should be used for linking life cycle and life cycle stage terms to their taxon-specific counterparts.\n+\n+## Changes\n+\n+- Updated `src/ontology/bridge/bridges.rules` so descendants of `UBERON:0000104` (`life cycle`) and `UBERON:0000105` (`life cycle stage`) set `TAXREL` to `RO:0002162`.\n+- Updated the dedicated XAO life-stage bridge rule in `src/ontology/bridge/bridge-xao-ls.rules` to generate `RO:0002162 some NCBITaxon:8353`.\n+- Updated the older bridge-generation scripts in `src/scripts/` and `src/ontology/` so life-cycle xrefs use `in_taxon` rather than `occurs_in` when that path is used.\n+- Refreshed the affected checked-in bridge OWL products so existing life-stage bridge axioms now use `RO_0002162`:\n+  - `uberon-bridge-to-fbdv.owl`\n+  - `uberon-bridge-to-wbls.owl`\n+  - `uberon-bridge-to-xao.owl`\n+  - `uberon-bridge-to-zfs.owl`\n+  - `uberon-bridge-to-sslso.owl`\n+\n+## Validation\n+\n+- Verified relevant identifiers in the local ontology context, including `UBERON:0000104`, `UBERON:0000105`, `RO:0002162`, and `BFO:0000066`.\n+- Confirmed the affected generated bridge files no longer contain `BFO_0000066` in the life-stage bridge products that were changed.\n+- Ran Perl syntax checks on both bridge-generation script copies.\n+- Regenerated the SSSOM/T-OWL bridge rules from `taxa.py` successfully.\n+- Validated modified bridge OWL syntax with `robot convert`.\n+- Ran ELK reasoning with `robot reason --reasoner ELK` on each modified bridge OWL file.\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+- [x] Read issue context and comments.\n+- [x] Identified the rule path responsible for taxon-specific bridge generation.\n+- [x] Updated the generic and XAO-specific life-stage bridge rules.\n+- [x] Updated legacy xref bridge script behavior for life-cycle xrefs.\n+- [x] Refreshed affected checked-in bridge products.\n+- [x] Performed syntax, identifier, and reasoning validation.\n+\n+@dragon-ai-agent\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/e